Inspect your source code when the browser renders it. [Paragraphs][1] aren&#39;t allowed to contain `&lt;pre&gt;` elements so the browser tries to fix the invalid HTML for you and changes it to:

    &lt;p&gt;
      First paragraph.
    &lt;/p&gt;
    
    &lt;p&gt;
      &lt;/p&gt;&lt;pre&gt;Second paragraph with some preformatted code.
    &lt;/pre&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    
    &lt;p&gt;
      Third paragraph.
    &lt;/p&gt;

&gt; Paragraphs are block-level elements, and notably will automatically
&gt; close if another block-level element is parsed before the closing `&lt;/p&gt;`
&gt; tag.

Hence four paragraphs


  [1]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/p

